result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander O. VanZile was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Alexander O. VanZile is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Alexander O. VanZile was found guilty of Aggravated Battery-Intend Bodily Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(4).

Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. records.addlTxt: Defendant Alexander O. VanZile in court with attorney Lindsay L Erickson.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 4:44 PM. Called 15CM145 and 15CF157. Erickson is not listed on 15CM145 and court feels she was appointed for both cases and will proceed. Erickson no inaccuracies on ROAW paperwork. State's recites recommendation on the record, believes 11 days jail credit on CM case and 290 days jail credit on 15CF157, asks for a consecutive sentence to any other sentence currently serving. Erickson makes statement and asks for 1 1/2 years in the Wisconsin Prison System, serving 18 months of incarceration and 18 months on extended supervision asking for a concurrent sentence, argues DE needs treatment options, believes credit for 299 days combined. Court questions jail credit amount. Short discussion on jail credit. State makes final argument. Erickson makes final argument. VanZile makes statement, remorseful. Court proceeds to sentencing: 15CF157 - 6 years in Wisconsin Prison System - 3 years of incarceration and 3 years of extended supervision, concurrent to all sentences currently sitting (16CF200 and 16CM178), 290 days jail credit. Not eligible for programs. 15CM145 - 6 months in FC jail, consecutive to 15CF157, 11 days jail credit. Appeal rights given. Enter civil judgment for any unpaid fines.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Alexander O. VanZile in court with attorney William Allen Dickens. Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 11:00 AM. Called 15CF157 & 15CM145. State recites agreement 15CM145 - 1 year probation, $300 fine plus costs, restitution $137.48 includes 10% surcharge to be paid within first six months of probation, anger management, FT emp/schooling, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into bars. 15CF157 - Ct. 1 - 3 years probation with conditions of: 60 days in FC jail, victim is not present in the court room, no contact from victim and has not filed any VIS, no restitution will be ordered, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, FT emp/school, 100 hours community service, no contact with Tara Kane. Dickens and VanZile agree. State indicates any jail sentence should be retrowed back to June 2nd the day he plead and makes final statement. Dickens makes final argument and asks court to follow joint recommendation, 29 days credit if revoked, also asks for huber privileges, ICW hearing in future and asks to be released for that date. State and Dickens agree to concurrent sentence to current sentence VanZile is serving. Court sentences to the following: 15CM145 - Withhold sentence place on probation 1 year: conditions - AODA and follow through, anger management and follow through, FT emp/schooling, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, $300 fine plus costs, restitution $137.48 to be paid within first 6 months, bond was posted in 15CF157 and will be transfered to this case to be applied to restitution, to run concurrent to 15CF157.  15CF157 - with hold sentence place on probation for 3 years; conditions - 56 days in FC jail, with huber, concurrent with child support hold, 29 days jail credit if revoked, AODA and follow through, FT emp/schooling, no consumption or possession of alcohol, no entry into any bars or taverns, 100 hours of community service, costs, DNA (w/expunction verbage on DNA), no contact with Tara Kane. Firearm/voting restrictions and right to appeal given.
Sentencing hearing on June 6, 2016 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Alexander O. VanZile in court with attorney William Allen Dickens.  Defendant Alexander O. VanZile in custody.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 3:19 PM. Called both 15CF157 and 15CM145. State - both matters are set for a JT on 6/6/16 but ready to proceed with plea today, have not been able to comply - 15CM145 - plead G/NC, 1 year probation, $300.00 fine plus costs, restitution of $137.48 without VW surcharge - to be paid within first 6 months of probation; 15CF157 - amend #1 to dismiss hate crime enhancer, plead G to amended count #1, dismiss count #2, with joint recommendation of 3 years probation with conditions of: 60 days jail imposed as condition of probation, court costs and restitution if any has been received plus additional probation conditions that would be recited at the sentencing hearing. Recess to fill out PLQ. Back on record at 3:31 PM. Vanzile plead NC to count #1 on 15CM145. Court dismisses count #2 on 15CF157 and amends count #1 to delete any reference to the count being a hate crime. Vanzile pleads G to amended count #1. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it and finds that the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived his constitutional rights by entering his plea and right to JT, accepts pleas, adjudges guilty, continues bond. State asks that the court remand the defendant to the custody of the sheriff for stated reasons (victim notification requirements). Court remands to the custody of the sheriff, sets both matters for sentencing hearing. State will file an Information on 15CF157 and Dickens waives reading of the late filing of the Information. Adjounred at 3:40 PM.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for June 6, 2016 at 10:30 am.
Jury trial on June 6, 2016 at 08:30 am.
